image.altText: a girl wearing a hood looks away from the camera towards a window with a fern in it

props.synopsis: Ruby's House is a rare example of a residential service which supports young people who may otherwise fall into homelessness or couch-surfing due to family conflict.

title.children: Unique 'circuit-breaker' program keeping 8 to 15-year-olds out of homelessness

image.altText: A woman with a blonde bob in a face mask hold up two proof of disability cards.

props.synopsis: The founder of Invisible Disabilities Australia says she was "treated appallingly" while going through security at the Canberra Airport, after which she was wheeled into "what can only be described as a cupboard" to be pat down.

title.children: Invisible disability organisation founder says she felt 'violated' going through Canberra Airport security

image.altText: A sign on the front of a building saying 'Genius Childcare', photographed through bars.

props.synopsis: More than a dozen staff at Genius Childcare centres in the ACT have resigned while others have taken stress leave amid allegations of ongoing pay delays.

title.children: Mass resignations at national childcare chain over allegations staff aren't being paid on time

image.altText: A public bus with a wrap on the back that reads "MyWay+".

props.synopsis: From their new position on the crossbench, the Greens are backing calls for the Assembly to review the controversial transport ticketing rollout.

title.children: Transport Canberra had 'high degree of confidence' in MyWay+ system weeks before problematic rollout

image.altText: Head shot of a man with slicked-back blonde hair.

props.synopsis: Kristian White, who was found guilty last week of the manslaughter of Clare Nowland, 95, has been removed from the NSW Police Force by Commissioner Karen Webb.

title.children: Kristian White, who tasered Cooma great-grandmother, sacked from NSW Police Force

image.altText: A man with grey hair in a navy suit looks serious.

props.synopsis: University of Canberra interim vice-chancellor Stephen Parker, who was brought on in September to prepare a 2025 budget addressing the university's difficult financial position, has resigned from the role.

title.children: University of Canberra vice-chancellor resigns, citing 'lost confidence in council'

image.altText: A photo of a regional city with trees and power lines in the foreground

props.synopsis: Nearly 13,000 customers lost power across the far west of NSW this morning after a fault in the electricity network. Some businesses say the uncertainty was too much after experiencing rolling blackouts in October.

title.children: Outback NSW region beset by rolling blackouts for several weeks loses power again

image.altText: A woman with voluminous hair taking an image of herself in a bathroom mirror.

props.synopsis: Set against the backdrop of social change in the 1970s, Carol Jerrems's photography charted the women's movement, documented First Nations activism, put a spotlight on youth subcultures, and explored the era's music and arts scenes.

title.children: Era-defining photos of cultural icons and 'languid hangouts in share-house backyards' go on display

props.synopsis: Several teenagers were injured when a second-floor deck at a holiday rental in NSW South Coast town "gave way" during a party attended by about 40 people, according to a witness.

title.children: Teen describes screams as AirBnB balcony collapses, injuring partygoers on NSW South Coast

image.altText: A pink piggy bank sits right of centre against a stark white background.

props.synopsis: Millions of Australians will be able to tap their super fund for more financial advice about their retirement and superannuation, under changes being announced by the federal government, but they will have to pay for the benefit.

title.children: Super funds to charge members fees for 'new class' of limited financial advice under proposed laws

image.altText: A selfie of a man with his face blurred

props.synopsis: Anne and a man she had met online messaged every day for weeks. Their chat history shows how scammers emotionally and psychologically manipulated her — and stole $46,000.

title.children: 'You've destroyed me': A 'pig butchering' scam drained a 26-year-old Australian of $46,000

image.altText: Taweechai Thongrod uses distilling equipment to check his alcohol.

props.synopsis: After the deaths of six young backpackers, including two Australians, due to methanol poisoning in Laos, a distiller explains how untrained or unscrupulous brewers can easily create a deadly concoction.

title.children: The simple step when making alcohol that can be the difference between life and death

image.altText: Donald Trump frowns as he looks off camera while Xi Jinping stands behind him.

props.synopsis: Donald Trump has already started making threats that could kick off a trade war with the world's second-largest economy. But Beijing has been laying the groundwork for the prospect of another battle for some time.

title.children: Trump will likely restart his trade war with China when he becomes president, but this time Beijing is ready

image.altText: The exterior of a Commonwealth Bank branch including the brand's logos.

props.synopsis: Some Commonwealth Bank customers who withdraw cash at branches or post offices will soon be charged $3 for the privilege, after the bank announced it was migrating a legacy everyday account to a newer offering.

title.children: Commonwealth Bank urged to rethink 'terrible decision' to charge cash withdrawal fee

image.altText: People waiting in line to view a rental property

props.synopsis: Experts say while it does look like the market is cooling, any decrease in prices is still a long way off for renters.

title.children: Australia's rental market beginning to too cool, but relief is still a long way off

image.altText: Ryan Kobayashi and two women hold pictures of missing woman Hannah Kobayashi.

props.synopsis: Hannah Kobayashi has been seen crossing into Mexico alone with her luggage and is no longer is considered missing, according to police.

title.children: Hannah Kobayashi declared voluntary missing person after being spotted entering Mexico

image.altText: An image of Scott Rush, Matthew Norman, Chen Si-Yi, Martin Stephens, and Michael Czugaj

props.synopsis: Australia's home affairs minister and Indonesia's top law minister say there is a lot of goodwill to seal an unprecedented prisoner transfer for the five remaining members of the Bali Nine drug smuggling group — despite a lack of laws to facilitate it.

title.children: Remaining Bali Nine members unlikely to be transferred before end of year, as discussions continue

image.altText: Zhalin Cecil works with young boys at risk of perpetrating violence.

props.synopsis: Experts say comprehensive one-on-one early intervention programs are having positive outcomes for young males at risk of becoming adults perpetrators of family violence.

title.children: Teen boys tracking girlfriends, reading texts a pathway to family violence, experts warn

image.altText: A composite image shows the faces of three men, two with spectacles and one with a beard.

props.synopsis: Despite the risk of reprisals, five men speak out about allegedly suffering violence and threatening behaviour from Israeli forces in the West Bank city of Hebron.

title.children: Bashed, whipped, threatened and detained — five victims of alleged Israeli brutality in the West Bank

image.altText: A bowl of bright green powder.

props.synopsis: Matcha's vibrant colour and health benefits have made it a new fad food, fuelling a surge in demand that is outpacing supply.

title.children: Cafes and suppliers say matcha demand outpacing supply

image.altText: Max Jorgensen celebrates

props.synopsis: A year ago, Rugby Australia was still reeling from the fallout of a shocking Rugby World Cup exit. But 12 months on, improved performances suggest the Wallabies will be competitive enough to make the most out of the British and Irish Lions opportunity.

title.children: The Wallabies are turning a corner and that's vital to capitalise on British and Irish Lions opportunity

image.altText: Tigest beams as she smiles in front of a brewery wearing gold skirt and matching top with a blue pattern, her long braids down.

props.synopsis: Three years ago, the author was watching Twilight and daydreaming about a world in which there were more Black vampires. Now she's written a New York Times best-selling romance novel rooted in the Ethiopian myths and culture she was raised on.

title.children: Tigest wasn't sure anyone would be into Black vampires, but her debut novel is an NYT bestseller

image.altText: An officer holding a plastic bag containing smaller bags of white powder.

props.synopsis: Australia's largest specialist medical society has called for a number of illicit drugs to be decriminalised across the country.

title.children: 'Whole of society discussion': Peak specialist medical body issues demand for drug decriminalisation

image.altText: A Forestry machinery

props.synopsis: Right to information documents show the Tasmanian government has offered the state's public forestry company access to 39,000 hectares of native forest for logging, including old-growth areas and tracts of forest home to endangered species of animals.

title.children: Documents reveal plans to make 39,000 hectares of native Tasmanian forest available for logging

image.altText: A woman stands on a road caked with mud in front of a destroyed home after a flood

props.synopsis: More than 30 people have been killed in the flooding which was caused by heavy rains in the region in the past week, with communities facing a significant rebuild also preparing for more rain this weekend.

title.children: Deadly flooding in Malaysia and southern Thailand sees people urged to reconsider travel

image.altText: The glass facade of a court building bearing a coat of arms.

props.synopsis: The court heard the Sunshine Coast woman was unaware she was committing an offence by failing to report the alleged abuse.

title.children: Mother sentenced for failing to report alleged sexual abuse of eight-year-old daughter

image.altText: Elon Musk wears a serious expression.

props.synopsis: A judge has ruled that Elon Musk still is not entitled to receive a $86.6 billion compensation package even though shareholders of the electric vehicle company had voted to reinstate it earlier this year.

title.children: 'The ruling is wrong, and we're going to appeal': Tesla reacts after US judge again rejects Elon Musk's $86 billion pay package

image.altText: A blonde woman in a blue suit

props.synopsis: Ashley Alsione Ruscoe entered the pleas in Downing Centre Local Court this week, admitting to one count of domestic violence-related assault and one count of stalking or intimidation with intent to cause fear.

title.children: Boxer Harry Garside's ex-girlfriend pleads guilty to assaulting him, apprehended domestic violence order in effect

image.altText: A woman in a blue shirt wears a face mask and is being led by police officers in green uniforms through a courtroom

props.synopsis: A court upholds the death penalty sentence against real estate tycoon Truong My Lan as she scrambles to repay billions of dollars.

title.children: 'It makes me shake all over': Alleged fraud victims react after Vietnam's former richest woman loses appeal against death penalty

image.altText: Man with hiking gear smiles and points back/upwards at a mountain full of snow with ski tracks

props.synopsis: Three mountain climbers are missing after they failed to return from a planned ascent of New Zealand's highest peak.

title.children: Search underway for three climbers missing on New Zealand's highest peak

image.altText: Australia batter Alex Carey plays a pull shot during a Test against India.

props.synopsis: Australia wicketkeeper Alex Carey says he is surprised by the intense reaction to the first-Test loss against India, saying the team has plenty of time to bounce back in the five-Test Border-Gavaskar series.

title.children: Alex Carey and Australia staying calm amid storm over opening loss to India

image.altText: Michelle Heyman high-fives Hayley Raso while playing for the Matildas.

props.synopsis: Interim Matildas coach Tom Sermanni says the team is not particularly well-set-up for the future after having such a settled line-up for the past decade.

title.children: Matildas coach says the team hasn't 'planned for the future well enough'

image.altText: Trams moving along line in opposite directions on a quiet city street.

props.synopsis: A fallen electrical wire exposing faulty components has halted testing on the $2.9-billion Parramatta light rail project.

image.altText: Empty supermarket shelves.

props.synopsis: While shoppers at some Woolworths stores are still encountering empty shelves, the supermarket giant has filed an urgent application with the Fair Work Commission.

title.children: Woolworths reports $50m hit to sales as industrial dispute leaves supermarket shelves bare

image.altText: A man addresses a court with a gallery of people behind him and a chandelier overhead.

props.synopsis: Vanuatu has urged the International Court of Justice to find polluting nations have acted unlawfully by contributing to climate change, in a landmark case that could change future climate talks.

title.children: Vanuatu and Australia diverge in landmark ICJ climate change case
